msgid "The numeric type offers to do calculations with arbitrary precision. See <xref linkend=\"datatype-numeric\">for the equivalent type in the <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>server. Because of the arbitrary precision this variable needs to be able to expand and shrink dynamically. That's why you can only create numeric variables on the heap, by means of the <function>PGTYPESnumeric_new</function>and <function>PGTYPESnumeric_free</function>functions. The decimal type, which is similar but limited in precision, can be created on the stack as well as on the heap.</xref>"
